iGophernicus allows you to execute in-line scripts in your		gopher.black	70
igophermaps. That means you can do something like this:		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
i=ls -1r | grep -v 'gophermap' | awk '{printf "0%s\t%s\n", $1, $1}'		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
